00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:44.030
it would mean if Douglas
Adams were onto something.

00:01:44.030 --> 00:01:46.380
What if the Earth, and
the rest of the universe,

00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.190
for that matter,
were a computer.

00:01:48.190 --> 00:01:51.250
I mean, I know it sounds batty,
but battier things are true.

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:55.130
Angler fish are thing, and,
uh, Arrest Development is back.

00:01:55.130 --> 00:01:57.662
So how might it be that
the universe computes?

00:01:57.662 --> 00:01:58.620
Well, let's start easy.

00:01:58.620 --> 00:02:00.640
What does a computer
do, exactly?

00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:02.640
It operates on
information, it engages

00:02:02.640 --> 00:02:04.690
in processes-- mechanical
and electrical--

00:02:04.690 --> 00:02:05.971
that make decisions.

00:02:05.971 --> 00:02:08.470
Those decisions are based on
programs, which at their heart,

00:02:08.470 --> 00:02:10.930
are bits-- just
little 1s and 0s.

00:02:10.930 --> 00:02:13.210
The output of the program
is fed back into the system,

00:02:13.210 --> 00:02:15.700
and the information processing
and creation continues.

00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:18.410
What, by comparison,
then, is the universe?

00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:20.940
Well, it's nothing if
not information, right?

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:23.380
Sure, it's galaxies and stars
and planets and dolphins

00:02:23.380 --> 00:02:25.000
and towels, but
all of those things

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.291
are just made up of atoms,
which themselves are made up

00:02:27.291 --> 00:02:30.570
of particles in different states
that describe all of the stuff.

00:02:30.570 --> 00:02:32.610
Furthermore, the
universe is certainly

00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:34.360
the processes which
create and operate

00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:35.690
on all of that information.

00:02:35.690 --> 00:02:36.190
#Phisics.

00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:37.930
Now, this whole
idea really starts

00:02:37.930 --> 00:02:40.970
to take shape once we get down
to the nitty gritty, or itty

00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:42.620
bit-y, as the case
may be-- emphasis

00:02:42.620 --> 00:02:44.980
being on bi-t-- bit-ty.

00:02:44.980 --> 00:02:45.900
[BA-DUM CHING]

00:02:45.900 --> 00:02:47.750
Remember all of those 1s and 0s?

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:50.620
As it turns out, the way they
behave inside a normal computer

00:02:50.620 --> 00:02:52.440
is pretty comparable
to the way atoms

00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:54.545
behave inside a
universe computer.

00:02:54.545 --> 00:02:56.420
Now, it's true that our
ontological metaphors

00:02:56.420 --> 00:02:59.730
tend to follow whatever the in
vogue technology of the day is.

00:02:59.730 --> 00:03:01.740
The human brain and the
universe have variously

00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:03.960
been described as books
and libraries, clocks

00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:04.610
and factories.

00:03:04.610 --> 00:03:07.550
But this one, the computer,
has some pretty convenient

00:03:07.550 --> 00:03:08.284
correlations.

00:03:08.284 --> 00:03:10.700
Like how the universe and its
atoms, much like a computer,

00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:12.560
have a binary foundation.

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:15.310
Theoretical physicist and
Niels Bohr bro, John Wheeler,

00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:16.350
put it like this.

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:18.570
"It is not unreasonable to
imagine that information

00:03:18.570 --> 00:03:20.445
sits at the core of
physics," in the same way

00:03:20.445 --> 00:03:22.320
"it sits at the
core of a computer.

00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:23.800
It from bit.

00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:25.800
Otherwise put, everything
'it'-- every particle,

00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:28.410
every field of force, even the
space-time continuum itself--

00:03:28.410 --> 00:03:29.930
derives its function,
its meaning,

00:03:29.930 --> 00:03:33.650
its very existence entirely from
the apparatus-elicited answers

00:03:33.650 --> 00:03:37.160
to yes or no questions,
binary choices, bits."

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:39.180
'It from bit' has
become a kind of mantra

00:03:39.180 --> 00:03:41.180
in a sometimes controversial
line of thinking,

00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:42.920
variously called
digital physics,

00:03:42.920 --> 00:03:44.680
digital philosophy,
digital ontology,

00:03:44.680 --> 00:03:46.334
digital-- so on and so forth.

00:03:46.334 --> 00:03:48.000
These theories hold
that nature performs

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:51.410
or is the result of calculation,
meaning that nature, the Earth,

00:03:51.410 --> 00:03:53.370
maybe even our brains
are deterministic.

00:03:53.370 --> 00:03:54.910
They are programmed.

00:03:54.910 --> 00:03:56.960
They are the moving
parts or the result

00:03:56.960 --> 00:04:00.459
of a process, which is run
by a program that has a goal.

00:04:00.459 --> 00:04:03.000
This idea is huge, and we can't
give at the time it deserves.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:04.500
So if you want to more,
we'll put a reading list

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:05.180
in the doobly doo.

00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:07.400
Now, assuming that you're
sufficiently convinced of,

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:09.549
or intrigued by, the idea
of the universe computer,

00:04:09.549 --> 00:04:11.590
we can start talking about
the interesting stuff,

00:04:11.590 --> 00:04:13.610
like, what is it computing?

00:04:13.610 --> 00:04:15.550
What is the goal of the program?

00:04:15.550 --> 00:04:17.430
Maybe it is the heat
death of universe.

00:04:17.430 --> 00:04:19.860
Its goal probably
isn't the computation

00:04:19.860 --> 00:04:21.839
