whose answer is 42.

00:04:21.839 --> 00:04:26.020
But what it is, it
involves us-- like, people.

00:04:26.020 --> 00:04:28.560
Douglas Adams even described
Earth through deep thought

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:31.130
as a computer of such
infinite and subtle complexity

00:04:31.130 --> 00:04:33.310
that organic life
itself will form

00:04:33.310 --> 00:04:35.350
part of the operational matrix.

00:04:35.350 --> 00:04:37.510
So that could mean two things.

00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:39.579
Maybe that organic
life is passive,

00:04:39.579 --> 00:04:41.120
and the simulation
argument is right,

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:42.580
and we're all currently
plugged into the matrix,

00:04:42.580 --> 00:04:43.996
and not actually
here, and there's

00:04:43.996 --> 00:04:46.430
nothing you can do about
it, so just don't panic.

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:48.470
Or it could mean
that organic life

00:04:48.470 --> 00:04:50.680
is active in that calculation.

00:04:50.680 --> 00:04:54.480
Meaning, we live in or are
a discretized operationally

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:57.110
complex system composed
not of matter and energy

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:59.610
but of bits and algorithms.

00:04:59.610 --> 00:05:02.620
And that life, and all of its
endeavors-- like science, art,

00:05:02.620 --> 00:05:04.810
getting really good at
bocce, Douglas Adams positing

00:05:04.810 --> 00:05:06.130
that the answer to life,
the universe, and everything

00:05:06.130 --> 00:05:09.470
is 42-- are all just a pursuit
of whittling down our theories

00:05:09.470 --> 00:05:12.790
about the way the world works
into computable, indisputable

00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:13.466
truths.

00:05:13.466 --> 00:05:14.840
The purpose of
the program, then,

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:16.690
